<h2>Java Example Program</h2>
The following two web pages are important.  They contain
nearly all of the information a java programmer might need
about the various java library classes.

<ul>
<li><a href="http://java.sun.com/">Main Java Sun Web Page</a>
<li><a href="http://java.sun.com/reference/api/index.html">Java Sun API
Specification Page</a>
<li><a href="http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.4.2/docs/api/">Alphabetical 
Listing of Java Library Classes</a>
</ul>
<p>

<h3>Compiling and running a java program</h3>
<ul>
<li>To create a java program, you must have the name of the
class in the file to be the same as the name of the file.
<p>
<li>To compile the program use the command <b>javac</b> as in:
<pre>
    javac HelloWorld.java
</pre>
This will take the source code in the file HelloWorld.java 
and create the Java ByteCode in a file HelloWorld.class.
<p>
<li>To run the compiled program use the command <b>java</b> as in:
<pre>
    java HelloWorld
</pre>
Note that you do not use the any file extension in this command.
<p>
</ul>
